#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cdeveloper%5Ctriplydb-publish-implementation.md:77
msgid "Token storage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cdeveloper%5Ctriplydb-publish-implementation.md:79
msgid ""
"The API token is stored in `localStorage` under a namespaced key. It is read "
"when the dialog opens and cleared when the user explicitly removes it. It is "
"transmitted only to the configured TriplyDB base URL over HTTPS — never "
"logged or sent elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cdeveloper%5Ctriplydb-publish-implementation.md:83
msgid "Graph accumulation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cdeveloper%5Ctriplydb-publish-implementation.md:85
msgid ""
"TriplyDB auto-numbers graphs on each upload (graph1, graph2, ...). Direct "
"SPARQL UPDATE and HTTP PUT approaches to accumulate into a single graph both "
"return 403 or 405. The current solution is a backend proxy that queries all "
"graphs and presents a unified view."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cdeveloper%5Ctriplydb-publish-implementation.md:87
msgid "The proxy endpoint: `{backendUrl}/v1/services/update`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cdeveloper%5Ctriplydb-publish-implementation.md:89
msgid ""
"If the proxy is unavailable, the upload still succeeds. A warning is shown: "
"\"Service update failed — data is accessible in TriplyDB but the SPARQL "
"endpoint may not reflect the latest state.\" The proxy is optional; the "
"upload itself does not depend on it."
msgstr ""

