msgid "`ronl:ParameterWaarde`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:24
msgid "Configurable values that tune rule behaviour"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:32
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\rules-policy-parameters.md:32"
msgid "Rules layer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:34
msgid ""
"Rules are time-bounded (`ronl:TemporalRule`) business rules that implement "
"policy decisions. Each rule carries a mandatory identifier and title, an "
"optional URI, temporal validity dates (`ronl:validFrom`, `ronl:validUntil`), "
"a confidence level, and an extension reference (`ronl:extends`) that links "
"the rule to a specific article or version of the legal resource."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:36
msgid ""
"The dual typing `a cpsv:Rule, ronl:TemporalRule` ensures both CPSV-AP 3.2.0 "
"compliance and compatibility with Dutch RONL extensions."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:40
msgid "Policy layer (CPRMV)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:42
msgid ""
"The CPRMV tab captures normative rules extracted directly from legislation — "
"the values mandated by law rather than the computational logic that applies "
"them. These are modelled as `cprmv:Rule` and imported either by pasting JSON "
"(normenbrief format) or by filling in individual fields."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:44
msgid ""
"Each CPRMV rule has six mandatory fields: identifier, title, definition "
"(full legal text), situational context, the normative value itself, and the "
"legal source path (`cprmv:ruleIdPath`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:46
msgid ""
"An informational banner in the CPRMV tab shows the currently linked legal "
"resource and the `cprmv:implements` property that creates an explicit "
"semantic link between a policy rule and the versioned legislation it "
"implements — enabling clean SPARQL queries without fragile string parsing."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:50
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\rules-policy-parameters.md:50"
msgid "Parameters layer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:52
msgid ""
"Parameters are configurable constants that tune rule behaviour without "
"changing the rules themselves — for example, income thresholds, age limits, "
"or regional rates. Modelled as `ronl:ParameterWaarde`, each parameter "
"carries a machine-readable notation (`skos:notation`), a numeric value and "
"unit (`schema:value`, `schema:unitCode`), and optional temporal validity."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:56
msgid "Why this separation matters"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:58
msgid ""
"The RPP pattern creates a clear chain of traceability: **Law → Policy → Rule "
"→ Parameter → Decision**. The practical benefits are:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:60
msgid ""
"**Legal traceability.** Every decision can be traced back to the specific "
"article of legislation that mandates it. When legislation changes, the "
"affected layer is immediately identifiable."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:62
msgid ""
"**Organisational agility.** Parameters can be adjusted (e.g. a regional "
"pilot rate) without touching the rules or redeploying decision models. Rules "
"can be versioned without touching the underlying policy statements."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:64
msgid ""
"**Governance clarity.** Each layer has distinct ownership. Policy rules are "
"owned by legal teams, computational rules by analysts, and parameters by "
"operational teams. Approval workflows can be scoped to the layer that "
"actually changed."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Crules-policy-parameters.md:66
msgid "See [RPP Architecture Reference]{1} for the formal specification."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:1
msgid "Service, Organisation & Legal Definition"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:3
msgid ""
"The editor's three foundational tabs — Service, Organisation, and Legal — "
"cover the mandatory descriptive metadata required by CPSV-AP 3.2.0 for any "
"Dutch government public service."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:7
msgid "Service definition"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:9
msgid ""
"The Service tab captures metadata about the public service itself, modelled "
"as `cpsv:PublicService`. This is the anchor entity that all other data links "
"to."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:11
msgid ""
"Key fields include the service's unique identifier (used to construct RDF "
"URIs throughout the document), its official title and description, thematic "
"classification, sector (government level), language, keywords, and cost and "
"output specifications."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:13
msgid ""
"The identifier field has special significance: the editor sanitises it "
"automatically, replacing spaces with hyphens and removing invalid URI "
"characters. The resulting value is used as the base for every URI in the "
"exported Turtle file, so a stable, descriptive identifier is important."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:20
msgid ""
"The **Cost** and **Output** sections within the Service tab implement "
"`cv:Cost` and `cv:Output` from CPSV-AP 3.2.0, allowing services to document "
"fees and the deliverables citizens receive."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:24
msgid "Organisation management"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:26
msgid ""
"The Organisation tab models the competent authority responsible for the "
"service as `cv:PublicOrganisation` (CPSV-AP 3.2.0 compliant — formerly "
"`org:Organization`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:28
msgid ""
"The geographic jurisdiction field (`cv:spatial`) is mandatory under CPSV-AP "
"3.2.0. The editor enforces this and displays a validation error if it is "
"omitted."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:30
msgid ""
"Organisation logos can be uploaded directly in this tab. Uploaded images are "
"resized to 256×256px, encoded as base64, and — when publishing to TriplyDB — "
"uploaded as a named asset. The generated Turtle includes both `foaf:logo` "
"and `schema:image` properties. This creates a full semantic traversal path "
"from a DMN decision model to the organisation's logo: `DMN → Service → "
"Organisation → Logo`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:32
msgid ""
"The organisation identifier supports both short form IDs (e.g. `SVB`) and "
"full URIs. When a short ID is provided, the editor expands it to `https://"
"regels.overheid.nl/organizations/{id}`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:36
msgid "Legal resource linking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:38
msgid ""
"The Legal tab links the service to its statutory basis, modelled as "
"`eli:LegalResource`. Dutch laws are identified by their BWB ID (e.g. "
"`BWBR0002221`), which the editor validates against the expected pattern."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:40
msgid ""
"Fields include the BWB ID, the version or consolidation date, and an "
"optional title and description. The editor generates a structured ELI URI "
"for the legal resource, which the Rules and DMN tabs then reference to "
"establish traceability from decision logic back to legislation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cservice-organisation-legal.md:42
msgid ""
"The relationship between the service and its legal resource is expressed as "
"`cv:hasLegalResource` (changed from `cpsv:follows` in CPSV-AP 3.2.0)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:1
msgid "TriplyDB Publishing"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:3
msgid ""
"The editor can publish service metadata directly to a TriplyDB knowledge "
"graph without any manual file handling. The publish feature is available via "
"the **Publish** button in the bottom-right of the application."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:12
msgid "What publishing does"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:14
msgid ""
"When you publish, the editor generates the complete Turtle output for the "
"current service definition and uploads it to the specified TriplyDB dataset "
"via the TriplyDB API. A backend proxy then ensures the data is accessible "
"via a cumulative SPARQL endpoint — so each published service accumulates in "
"the dataset rather than overwriting previous entries."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:16
msgid ""
"Organisation logos, when present, are uploaded as named assets alongside the "
"Turtle data, making them available as linked resources in the knowledge "
"graph."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:20
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\triplydb-publishing.md:20"
msgid "Progress tracking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:22
msgid ""
"The publish dialog shows step-by-step progress with real-time status "
"indicators:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:24
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\triplydb-publishing.md:24"
msgid "Validating form"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:25
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\triplydb-publishing.md:25"
msgid "Generating TTL"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:26
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\triplydb-publishing.md:26"
msgid "Uploading to TriplyDB"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:27
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\triplydb-publishing.md:27"
msgid "Updating service via backend proxy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:29
msgid ""
"Each step transitions from pending to complete as it finishes. On success, "
"the dialog displays a direct link to the published dataset and closes "
"automatically after two seconds. Errors are surfaced inside the dialog with "
"details, and an inline message appears under the page title after the dialog "
"closes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:33
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:35
msgid ""
"Publishing requires four values: the TriplyDB base URL, account name, "
"dataset name, and an API token. The token is stored in browser localStorage "
"— it is never transmitted to any server other than the configured TriplyDB "
"instance."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:37
msgid ""
"An optional **Test Connection** button verifies credentials before "
"publishing, without uploading any data."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:41
msgid "Cumulative data storage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:43
msgid ""
"TriplyDB's default behaviour creates auto-numbered graphs on each upload. "
"The backend proxy addresses this by querying across all graphs and "
"presenting a unified view, so the dataset always appears to contain all "
"published services regardless of how many upload operations have been "
"performed."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:1
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\vendor-integration.md:1"
msgid "Vendor Integration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:3
msgid ""
"Government reference implementations of decision models are open-source and "
"validated by the responsible authority. Commercial vendors build their own "
"implementations on top of these reference models, offering enterprise "
"support, SLAs, and additional capabilities. The Vendor tab lets service "
"owners document these vendor implementations and their certification status "
"as part of the service's Linked Data record."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:7
msgid "Multi-vendor architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:9
msgid ""
"The vendor list is loaded dynamically from the RONL vocabulary in TriplyDB, "
"querying for all `ronl:MethodConcept` instances. This means new vendors "
"appear in the dropdown automatically when they are added to the vocabulary — "
"no editor update is required. Currently 17 vendor platforms are listed, with "
"full integration implemented for iKnow and the Blueriq metadata form serving "
"as the reference implementation for the broader pattern."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:11
msgid ""
"Each vendor implementation is modelled as a `ronl:VendorService`, linked to "
"the reference service via `ronl:basedOn` and to the implementing "
"organisation via `schema:provider`. The TTL output uses Schema.org and RONL "
"vocabularies for contact, technical, and certification metadata."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:15
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\vendor-integration.md:15"
msgid "iKnow integration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:17
msgid ""
"iKnow is a legislative analysis and knowledge management platform. The iKnow "
"integration allows field mappings from iKnow XML exports to CPSV-AP "
"properties to be configured and saved, then used to import actual iKnow data "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:19
msgid ""
"The integration works in two modes. In **Configure** mode, an example XML "
"file is uploaded and each XML field is mapped to the corresponding CPSV-AP "
"property for each editor section (Service, Legal, Rules, Parameters, CPRMV). "
"The configuration is saved as a reusable JSON file. In **Import** mode, the "
"actual iKnow data file is uploaded, the saved configuration is selected, and "
"the mapped data is previewed before importing into the editor."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:23
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor\\features\\vendor-integration.md:23"
msgid "Certification workflow"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:25
msgid ""
"The Vendor tab includes a certification tracking workflow. A vendor "
"implementation can be marked with one of several certification statuses. "
"When the status is set to `certified`, the certifying organisation "
"(typically the competent authority from the Organisation tab) and "
"certification date are required. A certification modal guides users through "
"this process."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:27
msgid ""
"The certification details are included in the Turtle output as "
"`ronl:certificationStatus`, `ronl:certifiedBy`, `ronl:certifiedAt`, and "
"`ronl:certificationNote` properties, making certification status queryable "
"via SPARQL."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:36
msgid "Adding new vendors"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cvendor-integration.md:38
msgid ""
"The architecture is designed for extension. Each vendor integration is a "
"separate component in `src/components/tabs/vendors/`, rendered conditionally "
"based on the selected vendor URI. Adding a new vendor integration requires "
"creating the vendor-specific form component, implementing its data parser, "
"creating a field mapping configuration, and adding state management — "
"without modifying any existing vendor components."
msgstr ""

