msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:39
msgid "The typical workflow for a new service definition follows these steps:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:41
msgid ""
"**Fill in Service Details** — Enter the service identifier, official name, "
"description, and sector. The identifier becomes the base for all RDF URIs in "
"the output, so choose something stable and descriptive (e.g. `aow-"
"leeftijdsbepaling`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:43
msgid ""
"**Add Organisation** — Enter the competent authority. The geographic "
"jurisdiction (`cv:spatial`) is mandatory."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:45
msgid ""
"**Link Legal Resource** — Enter the BWB ID of the governing legislation "
"(e.g. `BWBR0002221`). The editor validates the format and constructs the ELI "
"URI."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:47
msgid ""
"**Define Rules** *(optional)* — Add temporal rules that implement the legal "
"resource."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:49
msgid ""
"**Add Parameters** *(optional)* — Add configurable constants used by the "
"rules."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:51
msgid ""
"**Add Policy (CPRMV)** *(optional)* — Import or enter normative rules "
"extracted from the legislation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:53
msgid ""
"**Validate** — Click the **Validate** button to check for errors. Missing "
"mandatory fields are highlighted."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:55
msgid ""
"**Download TTL** — Click **Download TTL** to export the compliant Turtle "
"file."
msgstr ""

