#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:47
msgid ""
"On success, a direct link to the published dataset appears and the dialog "
"closes automatically after two seconds. A green message with the dataset URL "
"appears under the page title and auto-dismisses after ten seconds."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:51
msgid "Error handling"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:53
msgid ""
"Errors are displayed inside the dialog with details. The dialog closes after "
"five seconds and an inline red message appears under the page title. Common "
"causes include invalid credentials, a non-existent account or dataset name, "
"or network issues."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:57
msgid "API token security"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:59
msgid ""
"Your API token is stored in browser localStorage on your device only. It is "
"transmitted exclusively to the configured TriplyDB API endpoint over HTTPS. "
"It is never sent to any other server."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:61
msgid "Best practices:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:62
msgid ""
"Create tokens with the minimum permissions needed (write access to the "
"specific dataset)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:63
msgid "Rotate tokens regularly via TriplyDB → User Settings → API Tokens"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:64
msgid "Never share tokens or commit them to version control"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:68
msgid "Cumulative publishing"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cpublishing-to-triplydb.md:70
msgid ""
"Each time you publish, the service data is added to the dataset. The backend "
"proxy provides a unified SPARQL endpoint that queries across all uploads, so "
"the dataset always reflects the complete current state of all published "
"services. Publishing the same service again after edits results in the "
"updated version being available alongside the previous one in TriplyDB, with "
"the unified endpoint showing the most recent data."
msgstr ""

